24:54.704 --> 24:57.487
You can have debate, but lack division.

24:58.348 --> 25:04.935
You can wrestle with a topic, hear experiences and opinions, and be respectful of other people, all while attacking arguments.

25:07.017 --> 25:08.559
We cannot take things personally.

25:10.161 --> 25:11.442
This is so important.

25:11.746 --> 25:15.371
We have the option to not take things personally.

25:18.155 --> 25:23.141
And that starts with, we make sure that when we're arguing, it's about primary matters.

25:25.024 --> 25:25.905
This is how it starts.

25:27.487 --> 25:36.059
The debate in Acts 15 is not about how Christians should engage the oppression of Rome.

25:36.079 --> 25:37.461
It's not about the tax system.

25:38.482 --> 25:41.266
It's not about what to wear to church.

25:41.410 --> 25:47.898
It's not about what you believe about when Jesus is coming back.

25:47.918 --> 25:55.868
They have a heated debate over who's in, who's out, and how do you stay in.

25:57.710 --> 26:04.678
Too often, we make secondary or tertiary or even periphery things, central.

26:05.820 --> 26:07.762
And we don't do it on purpose, often.

26:08.706 --> 26:15.553
But we get so personally invested in our own opinions that it becomes as if they are a primary issue.

26:16.974 --> 26:24.221
And if anybody disagrees with the way I see this periphery thing, periphery thing, then they're my enemy.

26:25.703 --> 26:27.164
Not so in the Christian church.

26:28.445 --> 26:30.427
It ought not to be in the Christian church.

26:35.092 --> 26:37.554
We go further in this when we

26:37.794 --> 26:45.484
get so personally invested in our opinions that we find people to oppose within argue with them, God help you on the internet sometimes.

26:46.386 --> 26:55.979
And then we take it upon ourselves to do our own research and find our own facts and be the final decision makers on the issue.

26:57.200 --> 26:59.564
But that's not what the Council of Jerusalem shows us.

27:01.026 --> 27:07.314
When the debate gets heated, when everybody recognizes this is too important to leave unsettled

27:08.194 --> 27:15.144
and too important to decide among ourselves, they go to trusted leaders who will trust in the Word of God.

27:16.607 --> 27:23.457
This debate is ultimately decided by Holy Scripture, the Holy Spirit, and leaders of character who trust in both.

27:25.159 --> 27:27.844
Now to even get to this point requires good character.

27:28.284 --> 27:34.834
Let's all be honest, to not take things personally requires some self-regulation that not everybody was raised with.

27:38.530 --> 27:39.992
It takes respect for other people.

27:40.873 --> 27:41.855
It takes self-control.

27:42.516 --> 27:45.921
It takes a willingness to say, I love you too much to try to win this argument.

27:47.383 --> 27:48.925
I'll tell this to my kids all the time.

27:48.965 --> 27:50.047
I ask my kids rather.

27:50.387 --> 27:51.168
What's more important?

27:51.909 --> 27:54.072
Winning this argument or winning your brother?

27:57.557 --> 28:02.104
And if it's not a primary thing, the answer cannot be winning the argument.

28:04.547 --> 28:06.450
Jesus said, blessed are the peacemakers.

28:08.642 --> 28:13.830
but peace is not made by avoiding conflict, or by starting a fight because you like winning.

28:15.232 --> 28:24.907
Peace is made by addressing conflict with kindness, respect, submission to the spirit, submission to Scripture, and abiding ourselves in abundant grace.

28:26.910 --> 28:34.482
Holy Scripture is all over this conversation, and the decision is made by the power of the Holy Spirit that's clear

28:34.978 --> 28:36.680
By the way, James replies.

28:36.700 --> 28:41.744
He makes these observations about what the text says, and then levies his decision.

28:41.784 --> 28:46.269
So they've had the debate, they've heard every side, and now comes the decision.

28:47.430 --> 29:04.466
Verse 19, James, the brother of Jesus, says, therefore, my judgment is that we should not trouble those of the Gentiles who turned to God, but should write to them to abstain from things polluted by idols, and from sexual immorality, and from what has been strangled, and from blood.

29:05.122 --> 29:07.365
So let's talk about the decision.

29:07.385 --> 29:11.671
We'll talk about the absomences in a moment, but let's talk about the decision.

29:12.973 --> 29:16.838
The summary decision to this debate, do Jews need to become Gentiles and Gentiles become Jews?

29:17.359 --> 29:21.925
May seem obvious to us in the 21st century, but in the 1st century it was not clear.

29:22.265 --> 29:30.576
The decision is this, followers of Christ from every nation are not defined by a set of prescribed rituals and customs, but by faith in Christ.

29:32.379 --> 29:34.802
Followers of Christ from every nation

29:34.882 --> 29:42.609
are not defined by a set of prescribed rituals and customs, but by faith in Christ.

29:42.629 --> 29:45.012
In other words, Jews do not need to become Gentiles.

29:45.072 --> 29:46.773
Gentiles do not need to become Jews.

29:47.154 --> 29:51.638
All are saved by grace through faith with no additional religious burden.

29:53.580 --> 29:58.024
Gentiles will not be included because they complete certain rituals, but because of faith in Christ.

30:00.346 --> 30:04.690
Jews are not required to drop all rituals and customs.

30:04.802 --> 30:08.368
but to carry them according to their convictions and the grace of Christ.

30:10.131 --> 30:12.094
Jews get to be Jews, Gentiles get to be Gentiles.

30:12.214 --> 30:13.115
All are saved by grace.

30:13.135 --> 30:14.097
There is no hierarchy.

30:17.623 --> 30:24.333
Peter says it, clearest, we believe that we will be saved by the grace of the Lord Jesus just as they will.

30:25.736 --> 30:32.306
If you've come into this room, not knowing much about Christianity or thinking you knew a lot like I did once,

30:32.930 --> 30:36.533
that it's a lot of do's and don'ts, and as long as I figure all those out, I'll be fine.

30:37.554 --> 30:38.996
You need to hear this loud and clear.

30:39.056 --> 30:46.323
To be a Christian means you belong to Christ, and it is a belonging that you cannot earn.

30:48.185 --> 30:51.047
And if you can't earn it, you can't lose it either.

30:55.452 --> 30:57.193
There are plenty of things you have to earn in life.

30:57.213 --> 30:58.675
You have to earn a driver's license.

30:59.536 --> 31:01.938
You earn entry into university.

31:02.754 --> 31:05.057
You keep those things by staying within the lines.

31:07.000 --> 31:11.127
But there are other things that you know already that you just receive.

31:11.727 --> 31:13.009
And then you learn how to do it afterward.

31:14.071 --> 31:15.633
You are a teammate.

31:16.495 --> 31:19.659
Then you learn how to be a teammate.

31:19.679 --> 31:21.021
You are a sibling.

31:21.722 --> 31:23.685
And then you learn how to love brothers and sisters.

31:23.986 --> 31:25.588
You are a grandparent.

31:26.590 --> 31:29.554
And then you learn how to relate to your grandchildren.

31:31.810 --> 31:35.516
to put a really fine point on this and at the risk of belaboring a point too late.

31:37.999 --> 31:42.646
No one in here just decided one day, you know what?

31:43.107 --> 31:49.557
I'm gonna buy a leash, put a bowl of food on the floor, and go to a park full of dogs without owning a dog.

31:51.760 --> 31:58.610
You do all of those things, not so you can have a dog, but you do all those things because you have a dog.

31:59.522 --> 32:02.726
You are a dog owner, therefore you do things that dog owners do.

32:04.768 --> 32:10.475
Putting a bowl of food on the floor, having a leash, going to the dog park, going on morning walks, buying a carpet cleaner.

32:13.339 --> 32:17.784
The change is not that I did all these things so I could earn the identity that I have.

32:18.826 --> 32:21.569
It's I'm doing these things because of what I've become.

32:25.213 --> 32:28.978
This is the rules and

32:29.186 --> 32:31.169
customs and things that you observe in Christianity.

32:31.509 --> 32:33.532
This is how we're meant to live.

32:33.592 --> 32:34.693
This is how we operate.

32:34.994 --> 32:36.536
I belong to the kingdom of God.

32:36.776 --> 32:38.839
Therefore, I live as a citizen of heaven.

32:40.000 --> 32:43.024
No one is in Christ because of rights, rituals, and customs.

32:44.186 --> 32:45.247
It's not hereditary.

32:46.229 --> 32:47.851
All our preteens and high schoolers in the room.

32:48.532 --> 32:50.354
You're not a Christian just because your parents are.

32:54.259 --> 32:56.242
It is given by Christ.

32:56.898 --> 32:59.461
and by choosing to respond to His grace.

33:01.003 --> 33:03.907
God is the prime mover in this story.

33:04.307 --> 33:05.949
We merely respond.

33:06.790 --> 33:13.679
We are trees in the mighty wind of God's mercy, blowing where He wills us to go.

33:17.043 --> 33:21.869
Peter says it best, we shall be saved through the grace of our Lord Jesus just as they are.

33:23.371 --> 33:24.352
This is the gospel.

33:24.432 --> 33:25.874
This is the word of the gospel.

33:26.466 --> 33:28.128
that they were debating and talking about.

33:29.550 --> 33:33.395
That while we were yet sinners, Christ died for us.

33:34.616 --> 33:39.182
That before you even knew you needed a savior, one came for you.

33:40.043 --> 33:44.268
Before you knew you needed to be healed, a healer showed himself.

33:45.129 --> 33:55.602
Before you even trusted that God existed, he showed himself by becoming a man and dying for your sins so that you could be forgiven, redeemed, and never have fear of death.

33:56.706 --> 34:08.341
Death, the thing that looms over all of us and puts fear in our hearts, God has said, will not have the final word if you trust in Him.

34:09.562 --> 34:16.711
The author of life offers you life through Christ Jesus and there's nothing you can do to earn it.

34:17.652 --> 34:21.637
I'm sorry overachievers, there's nothing you can do to earn it.

34:24.501 --> 34:25.362
All you can do

34:25.794 --> 34:27.335
is trust that it's true.

34:32.781 --> 34:35.463
Christ has died while we were yet sinners.

34:36.044 --> 34:36.344
Why?

34:36.404 --> 34:37.345
Why would He do that?

34:38.126 --> 34:38.846
Because He loves us.

34:40.628 --> 34:40.968
That's it.

34:42.450 --> 34:43.271
Because He loves you.

34:45.052 --> 34:53.000
And because He saw you before you were formed and He knew to dwell with you is going to be the joy of my heart.

34:53.060 --> 34:55.442
Therefore, I will endure the shame of this cross.

34:57.186 --> 34:58.227
so that you will have new life.

35:01.050 --> 35:02.292
He died, but he didn't stay dead.

35:02.352 --> 35:03.513
He rose on the third day.

35:04.694 --> 35:07.437
The author of life is alive forever.

35:07.478 --> 35:11.322
And all you have to do is call upon his name.

35:14.385 --> 35:15.747
All you have to do is call upon his name.

35:17.208 --> 35:22.494
You don't have to go to church and read your Bible and wear khakis to become a Christian.

35:24.457 --> 35:25.778
You have to trust in Christ.

35:27.106 --> 35:30.950
And then, because you trust in Christ, you will come to church, maybe on time.

35:33.694 --> 35:34.735
You will read your Bible.

35:35.055 --> 35:35.696
You will pray.

35:36.937 --> 35:37.898
Cackies are optional.

35:40.962 --> 35:42.444
The pleats are coming back in style.

35:43.985 --> 35:44.986
They will go away again.

35:48.410 --> 35:55.058
How we live in the church flows from who we are and who we are is because of what Christ has done for us.

35:55.810 --> 35:56.851
We don't earn this.

35:56.992 --> 35:59.915
We receive it gladly and live in light of it.

36:00.696 --> 36:02.679
This lifts all burdens.

36:03.500 --> 36:16.637
No man or woman in Christ is defined as such because of rigorous adherence to a standard, but because you call on the name of Jesus and he is mighty to save and mighty to keep you.

36:17.678 --> 36:23.506
Brother and sister, if you've come into this room full of shame because you have failed the standard this week,

36:24.706 --> 36:31.554
There is a Savior for you and His grace is sufficient for you and His blood is powerful to cleanse you of all sin.

36:31.594 --> 36:34.538
The debate is settled.

36:35.619 --> 36:37.622
The decision is made unanimously.

36:38.603 --> 36:41.466
All are welcome by faith through grace.

36:43.209 --> 36:47.834
And so the council makes this declaration of unity to the church in Antioch.

36:49.296 --> 36:54.322
Read with me in verse 23, the letter.

36:56.098 --> 37:03.450
The brothers, both the apostles and the elders, to the brothers who are of the Gentiles and Antioch, Assyrian, Cilicia, greetings.

37:05.593 --> 37:06.034
Stop there.

37:07.917 --> 37:11.542
Look how grace creates fellowship where there was one's dissension.

37:14.387 --> 37:17.812
The Jews who had the market cornered on what it means to know God.

37:19.074 --> 37:24.082
Say to the Gentiles and Antioch in the surrounding region, our brothers.

37:25.890 --> 37:27.852
your brothers right to you greetings.

37:28.793 --> 37:32.077
The Greek here actually could be translated, your brothers, the apostles.

37:32.717 --> 37:37.343
The apostles just called me brother.

37:40.406 --> 37:50.137
And they repeat this word brothers over and over, not only that, but they affirm the ministry of Paul and Barnabas by saying, we have sent back with you our beloved Paul and Barnabas.

37:51.738 --> 37:55.122
Love flows freely where grace abounds.

37:57.282 --> 38:00.745
The declaration is that we were all one family in Christ.

38:02.487 --> 38:06.531
And because the grace of Christ has done that, there is no burden for you.

38:07.792 --> 38:08.312
Be free.

38:10.394 --> 38:12.016
The new life, be free.

38:13.437 --> 38:16.320
They even go out of their way to point out.

38:16.360 --> 38:25.789
We have heard, verse 24, that some persons have gone out from us and troubled you with words unsettling your minds, although we gave them no instructions.

38:25.849 --> 38:26.770
They clarify.

38:27.298 --> 38:28.319
These people were not from.

38:28.459 --> 38:29.521
We did not tell them to do that.

38:31.543 --> 38:32.925
So disregard what you've heard from them.

38:32.985 --> 38:39.673
So it seemed good to us, to verse 25, having come to one accord, that one accord means unanimous.

38:40.373 --> 38:49.564
We are unified in this decision to choose men and send them to you with our beloved Barnabas and Paul, men who have risked their lives for the name of our Lord Jesus.

38:49.985 --> 38:52.127
We have therefore sent Judas and Silas.

38:53.969 --> 38:54.610
They're saying,

38:54.786 --> 38:56.809
Okay, the guys before, we didn't tell them to do that.

38:57.009 --> 38:58.992
These guys, we told them to do this.

38:59.733 --> 39:00.974
They're speaking with our voice.

39:03.097 --> 39:05.621
They will tell you the same things by the word of their mouth.

39:06.362 --> 39:13.832
It has seemed good to the Holy Spirit and to us to lay no greater burden on you than these requirements.

39:15.134 --> 39:16.576
And they are few.

39:16.656 --> 39:20.361
So there's no religious burden, but there are requirements.

39:21.562 --> 39:24.306
This may seem contradictory, but think for just a moment,

39:25.410 --> 39:42.507
When you became a member of that team, when you got married, when you added a family member, whether a sibling got married or you had a child or you adopted a child, when you added a family member, you weren't like, there was no burden of like, I have to do a bunch of stuff, but there are requirements.

39:42.527 --> 39:44.489
You have to sacrifice time and energy for these people.

39:44.970 --> 39:47.472
You have to readjust your expectations for these people.

39:47.933 --> 39:49.074
Things do change.

39:49.234 --> 39:52.317
So there are some requirements.

39:52.337 --> 39:53.138
And here they are.

39:54.466 --> 39:55.908
What if I just read this and just left it?

39:57.369 --> 39:57.850
That'd be fun.

39:58.470 --> 39:59.512
I'm not gonna do that.

40:00.813 --> 40:07.461
The requirements are this, that you abstain from what has been sacrificed to idols and from blood and from what has been strangled and from sexual immorality.

40:07.981 --> 40:10.063
If you keep yourselves from these, you will do well.

40:10.844 --> 40:11.105
Very well.

40:12.026 --> 40:12.887
Okay, so let's look at this.

40:13.307 --> 40:16.931
In summary, there's talking so much about blood, what is happening?

40:17.672 --> 40:21.256
In summary, what they're saying is, all right, all you Gentiles?

40:21.837 --> 40:23.058
No more pagan stuff.

40:24.642 --> 40:30.350
Everything they've listed here was really common practice in the temples of Roman gods.

40:32.253 --> 40:39.663
To shed the blood of an animal and then cover yourself in it, drink it, eat the animal while it's still got all of its blood in it.

40:40.063 --> 40:43.588
All that kind of wild stuff that right now, all of us are like, gross.

40:44.970 --> 40:48.635
The reason you're like, gross is because the Christian church got rid of all of that.

40:50.077 --> 40:53.362
Pagan stopped doing it because Christians made it unpopular.

40:55.202 --> 40:58.686
So don't take it as like, man, what a bunch of weirdos.

40:58.726 --> 41:00.108
That actually was the norm.

41:01.349 --> 41:02.150
That was the norm.

41:02.170 --> 41:13.403
It was the expectation to not engage in temple worship that involved the blood of animals and eating blood and sexual immorality, cult prostitution, to not engage in those things was the weird thing.

41:15.105 --> 41:18.869
And now the leaders of the church are saying, all right, you guys used to be pagans.

41:19.149 --> 41:20.771
You can't do that stuff anymore.

41:22.693 --> 41:23.154
Why?

41:24.290 --> 41:25.532
Why do away with all of it?

41:25.652 --> 41:27.795
Not that anybody hears like, man, shucks.

41:30.158 --> 41:33.422
But the Scriptures make very clear, blood holds the power of life.

41:34.403 --> 41:37.367
And there's only one person who can give you life.

41:38.449 --> 41:39.149
And that's Christ.

41:40.231 --> 41:43.976
And so all other engagement with blood is off the table.

41:45.538 --> 41:48.862
Because to do so would be engaged in pagan ritual.

41:48.902 --> 41:51.826
So these common things in

41:52.130 --> 41:55.134
pagan life are now expected to stop.

41:58.339 --> 42:08.795
Secondly, this is actually genius because it addresses the pagan practices, but it also helps out the Jewish brothers and sisters who had really strict codes of conduct and convictions about what foods they couldn't eat.

42:09.155 --> 42:12.961
See, in the ancient Near East, who you ate with was who you belong to.

42:14.063 --> 42:17.508
When you eat dinner with somebody, you're saying, you belong to me and I belong to you.

42:17.608 --> 42:18.930
We are connected.

42:19.970 --> 42:28.643
But if I have really strict religious convictions about what foods I can and cannot eat and you don't, we can't sit at table together.

42:30.226 --> 42:31.668
So how is that going to get resolved?

42:31.708 --> 42:42.725
Well, these prohibitions not only say pagan stuff's got to stop, but they make space for kosher law and therefore increase table fellowship.

42:42.745 --> 42:48.594
They increase who you can break bread with so that you can continue to affirm who you belong to.

42:49.890 --> 42:59.864
What the leaders in Jerusalem are saying to the Gentiles is, hey, your brothers, the Jews around you have really strict convictions about food.

42:59.904 --> 43:00.865
Don't offend them.

43:02.227 --> 43:02.628
Love them.

43:03.789 --> 43:04.891
Embrace those convictions.

43:06.313 --> 43:13.042
And by doing that, they're also saying to the Jews in these areas, you don't have to give this up if it hurts your heart to do so.

43:15.906 --> 43:17.328
So how do we make sense of any of this?

43:17.348 --> 43:19.230
Because again, I don't think any of you are like shocks.

43:19.270 --> 43:22.254
I got to stop strangling animals and then eating them whole.

43:23.756 --> 43:24.617
What do we do with this?

43:25.919 --> 43:26.300
We do this.

43:28.122 --> 43:31.626
You don't have to share the same convictions with the brothers and sisters around you.

43:32.708 --> 43:43.602
In this room, you do not have to share the same convictions on food, drink, celebration, but you should maintain compassion and understanding for those who have other perspectives.

43:44.578 --> 43:46.079
and watch out for idolatry.

43:47.981 --> 43:57.971
You do not have to hold the same convictions where scripture is not clear, but you do have to maintain compassion and understanding and watch yourself for idolatry.

43:59.652 --> 44:05.778
The church was then, is now, and especially here in our city, is a multicultural community.

44:06.819 --> 44:14.226
We come from differing backgrounds, spiritual, socio-economic, ethnic, even denominational backgrounds.

44:15.106 --> 44:25.159
So we're all gonna have differing opinions on practices about food, clothes, holidays, words we use, music we listen to, whether or not you take your shoes off when you get into the house.

44:26.881 --> 44:28.122
All of these will be different.

44:28.162 --> 44:32.888
We do not have to become a monoculture, but we must love.

44:34.751 --> 44:37.214
We must show patience and kindness and understanding.

44:37.454 --> 44:40.137
We must show compassion when convictions are different.

44:41.960 --> 44:43.922
We must keep no record of wrongdoing.

44:44.354 --> 44:50.263
but forgive as Christ has forgiven us and show mercy and abundance because mercy has been given to you.

44:51.745 --> 44:53.888
This is vital for Christian maturity.

44:55.130 --> 44:56.612
Young believers are gonna make mistakes.

44:58.334 --> 45:02.761
People from different backgrounds are gonna do things different and it's probably gonna offend you.

45:08.009 --> 45:11.794
To grow and show grace and not hold it against them.

45:12.642 --> 45:15.606
will make you more like Christ, because you will learn what love looks like.

45:17.047 --> 45:26.139
My season saints, though, you can't think that you've got the market cornered on holiness, because some of our expectations are fully cultural.

45:28.381 --> 45:37.813
The type of music we prefer, the way we prefer, people dress when they come to church, fully cultural, rather than biblical.

45:37.833 --> 45:41.778
And so we must be generous to all and kind.

45:42.146 --> 45:43.007
where we have differences.

45:44.708 --> 45:47.291
This is vital for maturity and it's vital for unity.

45:48.352 --> 45:51.996
Remember where grace abounds, unity abounds.

45:52.016 --> 45:54.458
And so hold fast to that grace that you would be unified.

45:54.858 --> 45:57.561
This is essential for mission.

45:57.941 --> 46:01.725
Our whole sermon series in the book of Acts is about the mission of God.

46:01.985 --> 46:04.328
We're talking a lot about in-house issues right now.

46:04.708 --> 46:09.372
But this is vital for mission because recognizing your freedom in Christ is good.

46:09.433 --> 46:10.994
It means you can eat with anybody.

46:11.458 --> 46:15.944
You can have coffee with anybody, but it also means you can make adjustments when necessary.

46:17.386 --> 46:20.751
It's vital that freedom is not flaunted for the sake of freedom.

46:21.652 --> 46:32.066
Witnessing to Jews, Muslims, Mormons, even recovering addicts may necessitate that for a time you put away things that you have the freedom to take part in.

46:34.309 --> 46:35.431
And that is love.

46:37.093 --> 46:38.655
And we must watch out for idolatry.

46:39.697 --> 46:40.498
Every culture.

46:40.802 --> 46:42.825
has a temptation to idolatry.

46:45.328 --> 46:48.111
In our culture, sex is an idol.

46:49.794 --> 46:54.640
And so all of us have to watch out for the idolatry of sexual relationships.

46:55.261 --> 46:58.865
On both sides, so I'm gonna talk to two different people right now and then I'm gonna close.

47:00.167 --> 47:05.414
On one end, Angelenos, we got a chill on the sex stuff.

47:06.936 --> 47:08.818
